any idea whats wrong?

item.title: Help with proxies
item.dc:creator: @Rictoo Rictoo
item.description:
@Rictoo wrote:

vbcoderx: Yes, all SOCKS5 proxies have 1080 as a port

Almost all Proxy Lists are a bot scanning, and many times it accidentaly puts a socks4 proxy into a socks5 list.
Don’t believe me? http://checker.freeproxy.ru/checker try one of the socks5 proxies with a non-1080 port and on the checker choose socks5 proxies on the drop down list

Read full topic

item.title: Help with proxies
item.dc:creator: @vbcoderx vbcoderx
item.description:
@vbcoderx wrote:

rictoo, i don’t agree that u say all socks5 proxy have the port 1080, just the majority of them do… I looked a t a socks5 proxy list on google and it isn’t. Also if it says error connecting to server on the proxy your using click login again untill u get in. Some proxy servers u don’t have to do this on but some you do. I’d also once u get in, log out and if u have to use the same method again to check the proxy server
